## The Week at a Glance

- 🔴 **High — Active SaaS threat campaign:** Microsoft Threat Intelligence has published a direct warning about ShinyHunters, a known criminal group using phone-based impersonation, supply-chain compromise, and misconfigured guest access to steal credentials and abuse OAuth connections across SaaS platforms, including Microsoft 365. Any organization using third-party SaaS integrations or allowing guest access should treat this as an active threat.
- 🔴 **High — Passkeys become the default sign-in method in Entra ID:** Microsoft is changing the default authentication experience away from passwords toward passkeys, and is introducing a new model for SMS and voice-based login. Organizations that have not yet planned for this transition face disruption to employee sign-in workflows and potential compliance gaps.
- 🟡 **Medium — AI agent governance now has formal tooling:** Microsoft has released generally available controls to manage AI agent identities and permissions the same way you manage employee accounts. Organizations deploying AI agents without these guardrails carry identity and access risk that cyber insurers and auditors are beginning to scrutinize.
- 🟢 **Low — GPT-5.6 now powers Microsoft 365 Copilot:** OpenAI's latest model is live in Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Copilot Chat. No action is required; licensed users will notice improved reasoning and more reliable multi-step task handling automatically.

*Sources: [Microsoft Threat Intelligence — ShinyHunters OAuth Abuse](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/13/defending-saas-based-applications-against-shinyhunters-oauth-abuse/) · [Microsoft Security Blog — Passkeys as Default in Entra ID](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/13/microsoft-entra-id-security-updates-passkeys-are-the-default-authentication-method-in-entra-id/) · [Microsoft 365 Copilot Blog — GPT-5.6 Now Available](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-365-copilot-blog/available-today-openai-s-gpt-5-6-in-microsoft-365-copilot/ba-p/4533152)*

