## What Your Employees Will Notice

- **Sign-in experience changes are coming.** Employees will begin seeing passkeys promoted as the preferred way to sign into Microsoft 365 and other Entra-connected systems. Some users who rely on SMS text codes or automated voice calls to verify their identity may find those options behaving differently or requiring re-enrollment. Proactive communication from IT before this rollout reaches your tenant will reduce confusion and support calls significantly.
- **Copilot is noticeably smarter.** Users with Microsoft 365 Copilot licenses will find that responses in Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Copilot Chat are more capable on complex, multi-step tasks. No action is needed; the upgrade to GPT-5.6 is automatic for licensed users.
- **Email recall now works across organizations.** Employees can now recall a mistakenly sent email even when it was sent to someone at a different company, not just within your own organization. This is a frequently requested capability. Users will see updated recall options in Outlook.
- **Cloud PC and virtual desktop connections are more stable.** Employees using Windows 365 or Azure Virtual Desktop over restrictive networks, VPNs, or unstable connections will experience fewer dropped sessions following the general availability of RDP Multipath with redundant TCP.
- **OWA Light will eventually disappear.** A small number of users who access email through a simplified browser-based interface called OWA Light should be transitioned to the standard Outlook on the web experience. IT can identify affected users before the retirement deadline is confirmed.

*Sources: [Microsoft Security Blog — Passkeys as Default in Entra ID](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/13/microsoft-entra-id-security-updates-passkeys-are-the-default-authentication-method-in-entra-id/) · [Exchange Team Blog — Cross-Tenant Message Recall](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/cross-tenant-message-recall-in-exchange-online/ba-p/4535800/) · [Windows 365 Blog — RDP Multipath GA](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/windows-it-pro-blog/rdp-multipath-with-redundant-tcp-is-now-generally-available-for/ba-p/4534610/)*

---

## What Your Help Desk Should Expect

- **Authentication re-enrollment requests will increase.** As passkeys become the default, employees who have never set up a passkey, or who rely heavily on SMS codes, will encounter prompts they have not seen before. Help desk staff should be briefed on the new sign-in flow and equipped with step-by-step guides before this change reaches end users. Expect elevated call volume in the first two weeks following any tenant-wide rollout.
- **"Why did my login change?" inquiries.** Even well-communicated changes to sign-in behavior generate tickets. Prepare a short FAQ and consider a proactive all-staff communication from IT leadership.
- **Copilot capability questions.** Users who have been working around Copilot's previous limitations may submit tickets asking whether a new behavior is a bug or intended. Brief the help desk that GPT-5.6 is a deliberate upgrade, not an error.
- **Email recall questions — cross-company scope.** Now that recall works across tenants, users will test its limits. Expect questions about when recall is and is not successful, particularly for external recipients using non-Outlook clients.
- **Virtual desktop connectivity complaints should decrease.** If your organization uses Windows 365 or Azure Virtual Desktop, the RDP Multipath improvement should reduce the volume of "my session keeps dropping" tickets over time, particularly from users on home networks or VPNs.
- **OWA Light redirect confusion.** Users who have bookmarked the OWA Light URL may begin encountering redirects or broken experiences as retirement approaches. Help desk scripts should be updated to direct those users to standard Outlook on the web.

*Sources: [Microsoft Security Blog — Passkeys as Default in Entra ID](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/13/microsoft-entra-id-security-updates-passkeys-are-the-default-authentication-method-in-entra-id/) · [Exchange Team Blog — Cross-Tenant Message Recall](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/cross-tenant-message-recall-in-exchange-online/ba-p/4535800/) · [Exchange Team Blog — OWA Light Retirement](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/upcoming-retirement-of-owa-light-in-exchange-server/ba-p/4534943/)*

