## Cost & Licensing

- **AI agent governance requires Entra ID P2 or Microsoft Entra Suite.** The new generally available controls for managing AI agent identities — including lifecycle management, access reviews, and least-privilege enforcement — sit within Entra ID Governance features. Organizations running Entra ID P1 only should confirm with their Microsoft account team whether a license upgrade is required before deploying AI agents in production.
- **Windows 365 for Agents is a new licensed product.** Microsoft has announced a dedicated Cloud PC environment purpose-built for running AI agents securely. This is a separate, billable service. Organizations evaluating agentic AI deployment at scale should request pricing and include it in next budget cycle planning.
- **Copilot GPT-5.6 upgrade is included at no additional cost.** Existing Microsoft 365 Copilot licensees receive the GPT-5.6 model upgrade automatically. No license change or additional spend is required.
- **SMS and voice authentication cost implications.** The restructured model for SMS and voice sign-in in Entra ID may carry per-use costs depending on your current authentication configuration. Finance and IT should review the new model together before it takes effect to avoid unexpected charges on your Azure bill.

*Sources: [Microsoft Entra Blog — AI Agent Identity Governance](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-entra-blog/govern-ai-agent-identities-and-access-the-same-way-you-govern/ba-p/4529302/) · [Windows 365 Blog — Windows 365 for Agents](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/windows-it-pro-blog/windows-365-for-agents-a-secured-execution-environment-for-ai/ba-p/4529336/) · [Microsoft Security Blog — Passkeys and New SMS Authentication Model](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/13/microsoft-entra-id-security-updates-passkeys-are-the-default-authentication-method-in-entra-id/)*

